Package tr.edu.ku.devnull.needforspear.Model.GameData

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Constants
    Constants interface is used to store all the necessary constants for the game.
    Constants.ArrayConstants
    Array constants for the selections.
    Constants.MessageConstants
    Constants for the method messages.
    Constants.ObstacleNameConstants
    Constants for the names of the obstacles.
    Constants.ObstacleNumberConstants
    Constants for the obstacle threshold.
    Constants.ProportionConstants
    Constants which are mainly used for the proportion purposes.
    Constants.SoundConstants
    Constants for the name of the sounds to be played.
    Constants.SpellNameConstants
    Constants for the names of the spells.
    Constants.SphereConstantSpeeds  
    Constants.UIConstants
    Constants which are mainly used for the UI purposes.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    GameInfo
    GameInfo is class to apply Information Expert Design Pattern into the game.
    GameMap
    GameMap is a class which contains the information required to create the map to be played on.
    Location
    Location is a class which contains the value of the x and y coordinates of an object.
    SavedMapEntry
    SavedMapEntry is a class which contains the information of a player and the map they want to save.
    Size
    Size is a class which contains the dimensions of an object.
    Speed
    OVERVIEW: Speed is a class which contains the value of speed on the x and y-axis of an object.
    SpeedTest  
  • Enum Summary
    Enum Description
    Difficulty
    Difficulty enum is created to get rid of from String comparisons.
    GameMode
    GameMode enum is created to not deal with string comparisons.
